HEADWORD: Sternson
<hw>Stern"son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Stern</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, and cf. <er>Stemson</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>The end of a ship's keelson, to which the sternpost is bolted; --
called also <altname>stern knee</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

